James Clerk Maxwell was  a Scottish  scientist in the field of mathematical physics, born on 13 June 1831 at Edinburgh. His discoveries helped usher in the era of modern physics, laying the foundation for such fields as special relativity and quantum mechanics. His most notable achievement was to formulate the classical theory of electromagnetic radiation, bringing together for the first time electricity, magnetism, and light as different manifestations of the same phenomenon. Maxwell's equations for electromagnetism have been called the "second great unification in physics", after Newton. In the millennium poll—a survey of the 100 most prominent physicists—Maxwell was voted the third greatest physicist of all time, behind only Newton and Einstein. 
Therefore, on this auspicious day, ISTE NIT Durgapur Student's Chapter pays homage to Sir James Maxwell for his achievements and contributions to the world of science.
#science #sciencetechnology 
#sciencefacts #sciencefiction

node.text: Have you ever wondered to discern the roman-fleuve, of the inventor of the World Wide Web? Yes, you are in the affirmative, I am speaking of Tim Berners Lee; who's magnificent glory, is providing us a luminescence, in our circadian. The conquistador of the OM, KBE, FRS, FREng, FRSA, FBCS, Sir Timothy John Berners Lee advocated a management system, which was implemented as the victorious and foremost communication between HyperText Transfer Protocol client and server via the internet. He is also the founder of the World Wide Web Foundation and a senior research Signior and the holder of the 3Com founders chairs at the MIT Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence Laboratory. He is also the director of the Web Science Research Initiative and a member of the advisory board of the MIT Centre of Collective Intelligence. Presently he is the founder and president of the Open Data Institute and an advisor of the social network MeWe. For his awesome savoir-faire, the Queen of Britain knighted him in 2004. Besides, he is the recipient of the numerous prestigious salutation for his eloquent brilliance which has aggrandized to it's utopian excellence.  Therefore, with high regards and dulia and latria in our souls, ISTE NIT Durgapur Chapter heralds Sir Timothy John Berner Lee on the propitious occasion of his birthday, and wish to the heavens, with the utmost grace in our hearts, so that we shall be showered by his divine aura, for many more years to come.

node.text:
World Environment Day is observed on 5th June each year in more than 100 countries. It is an opportunity to raise awareness and promote action on national environmental issues.  Every year, a different host city is nominated, allowing various countries to showcase the positive things being done nationally, regionally and internationally to promote sustainable practices and reduce the impacts of climate change. The theme for 2020 is “Time for Nature”, and will be hosted in Colombia in partnership with Germany.  Our environment is one of the most important aspects to survive on this planet and can make life sustainable. It is correctly said that ‘ the difference between animals and humans is that animals change themselves for the environment, but humans change the environment for themselves’. The environment is just like our neighbourhood, it's surrounding conditions influence us and modify growth and development. In the recent times ,  incidents like the Australian Bush Fire, Melting of Glaciers in the Antarctica and also the destruction of the Sunderbans due to the Cyclone has been a major threat to the ecological balance and  it has become an immediate task for everyone to know and implement ways to protect the environment and the ecosystem.
Therefore ,ISTE NIT Durgapur  urges  all to take a day off from work and join various campaigns to spread awareness about environment protection. This can help to avert the ruining of the environment caused in the past years, “Together we will make something different".
#enviromentday #environment #forest #animals #saveelephants #saveenvironment #saveanimals  #savewater  #forestphotography #forestfire #nitdgp #plants  #saveplanetearth #forestlife #environmentalart

“Data is the oil, some say the gold, of the 21st century”, Joe Kaeser said at a tech forum in Stockholm. 
But raw data in itself, is not of much use. Data Analytics is the science that enables us to navigate the oceans of raw data and come up with meaningful conclusions. And the art of analysing these conclusions and converting it to layman’s terms is called Data Storytelling. A subject as interesting as it’s name. 
So to help you to learn something new in this period of lockdown, ISTE NIT Durgapur brings you the rare opportunity to join a webinar on ‘Data Science and Analytics’ by _Mr. Vijay Pravin Maharajan_, a leading data storyteller based in Germany. 
As part of his job, Mr. Maharajan helps companies better understand and use their data to optimize the customer experience. He has been named among the ‘Top 40 data scientists under 40’ in India and has also been nominated as '20+ data scientists to follow in 2020' by AI Time Journal, USA. This January, he even gave a Ted talk at TEDx Deggendorf, Germany.

So save the dates to grab this unique opportunity

Date: 8th of June, 2020
Time: 7 pm (IST)

On Google Meet

For registration, check the link in bio. 
#dataanalytics #webinar #science #data #germany #google #googlemeet #tedx

Today's ambience is blessed with the divine chant of Allahu Akhbar; as the Muslims and every people of this whole world rises to commemorate the providential ceremony of Eid al-Fitr. The occasion begins with the first viewing of the crescent moon in the sky. The propitious festival of Eid, marks the end of the Ramadan Kareem's long month of fast. According to the doctrines of Islam, on this religion everyone is forbidden to have an empty appetite. The holy day of Eid al-Fitr is solemnized by performing Namaz, in congregations in the open areas in the Mosques; and every euphoric soul embraces each other, with the heart of ecstasy. There is sanctity everywhere, as everyone oaths to virtue, rectitude, and morality. Every soul on Earth gets refreshed on this very occasion when they pray to Allah for others.
Therefore, lSTE NIT Durgapur, with dulia and latria, in the hearts, heralds everyone, Eid Mubarak, with a warm soul and earnestly fervent every heart to spread amour and mellow.
#eidmubarak #festival

Hello peeps. Goodbyes are really heartbreaking and when it comes to our favourite seniors , It's very tough to bid farewell to them as varoius memories and emotions of our life are connected with them. Moreover they were our guides in our college life who helped us to bring out our hidden talents and also saviours in times of any trouble. In addition to this, Due to the current pandemic situation, we weren't even being gifted to bade goodbye to our beloved seniors and arrange a memorable farewell. 
Therefore, ISTE NIT Durgapur is here to fulfill your wishes through "Yaadein". Rules are simple :

Juniors can send us pictures with their favourite seniors either in group photos or just favourite seniors pictures with a goodbye message or any other thing which connects their bonding.
Inbox your message at http://www.facebook.com/istenitd along with your favourite pictures and we will post it.

We will be accepting responses till 22nd May. So grab this opportunity of bading goodbye to your beloved seniors and rejuvenate the memories with them.

The National Technology Day:-
"Any sufficiently advanced technology is indistinguishable from magic".
The providential ceremony of the 11th May , The National Technology Day, was coined by our late Prime Minister Shri Atal Bihari Bhajpayee, to commemorate the technological ethoes of India, over the years.The background of this great day , asseverates the saga of the test of Pokhran ll; The Trishul missile and Hansa 3 in 1998.Truely, this day embellishes the roman-flueve of technological onset in India. And inspires the euphoric souls to aggrandize the technological fields to it's zenith. This day is solemnized by honouring and crowning the experts and scientists , who has succoured us to the technological and scientific luminisence.  The Indian Society for the Technical Education , NIT Durgapur Chapter , therefore heralds the propitious occasion of "The National Technology Day", with immense fervent and ebullience and pledges to undertake measures , to glorify technological aura for aeons to come.
#nationaltechnologyday #tecnology #nationalday

Mother is not only a person who gives you birth or has brought you up from your childhood days. She isn't a person at all,she is an emotion, a feelings and a lots of love with whom you are connected eternally.There is a saying "God couldn't be every where, and therefore he made mothers", That's why every creature in this universe has a mother. If you don't have anything but a mother then you are the happiest and luckiest creature. A mother is the torchbearer in a child's life as she is a constant source of motivation and inspiration for him. She is the real gem of the society. A throne is congruous with the elegance of a mother for reverence and veneration. She is filled with kindness, generosity, compassion, integrity, willingness to be vulnerable and authenticity. No matter what she is true to herself, we are nothing out of her.  Thus ISTE  NIT durgapur wishes all mothers across the universe a 'Happy Mother's day'.Though a Mother's Day shouldn't be celebrated like an one day occasion rather all the 365 days in a year must be celebrated as Mother's Day.
#mothersday #mothernature #mothersdaygift #mothersday #joy #happymothersday

The Leige-Lord of modernism, The Autrach of Belles-Lettres whose every stroke of ink is indeed pulchritudinous. Through all of his works, he indoctrinated us to reconnoitre our quintessentials. Yes, he is the symphonist of Jana Gana Mana; the tunesmith of The Gitanjali, KaviGuru Rabindranath Tagore. It's his Eloquent linguistic glory which transcended the art in the most paradisical deiform. Tagore's craftsmenship in every arena be it fine arts, poems, stories, novels is euphoric beyond all the praises. As a humanist, universalist, he ardently denounced the British Raj and advocated independence. Being a libertarian and progressionist , he founded  the Viswa-University in Santiniketan to inspire the young minds. He is our Father, the omnipotent personna and our torchbearer who with his divine works guide us to luminisence.  On the providential and propetious  occasion of the 8th May , ISTE NIT Durgapur heralds The Great Soul, The Rabindranath Tagore , with dulia and latria in our hearts and bow down our heads to the lotus soul.
